    • getName

      public static String getName(Field field)
      Gets the name of the annotated field using the corresponding AnnotatedElementNameProvider strategy for the named annotation on the field. If no named annotations are present, then an empty string is returned. If no specified name is given by the name provider, the field name is returned.
      Parameters:
      field - annotated field to find name for
      Returns:
      annotated name of field

    • getName

      public static String getName(Parameter parameter)

If no named annotations are present, then an empty string is returned. If no specified name is given by the name provider, the parameter name is returned.
      Parameters:
      parameter - annotated parameter to find name for
      Returns:
      annotated name of parameter

    • getName

      public static String getName(Method method)
      Gets the name of the given annotated method using the corresponding AnnotatedElementNameProvider strategy for the named annotation on the method. If no named annotations are present, then an empty string is returned. If no specified name is given by the name provider, the method name is used with is, set, get, and with prefixes removed and the result being de-capitalized.
      Parameters:
      method - annotated method to find name for
      Returns:
      annotated name of method without is/set/get/with prefix

    • getName

      public static String getName(AnnotatedType annotatedType)
      Gets the name of the given annotated type using the corresponding AnnotatedElementNameProvider strategy for the named annotation on the type. If no named annotations are present or if no specified name is given by the name provider, then an empty string is returned.
      Parameters:
      annotatedType - annotated type to find name for
      Returns:
      annotated name of annotated type

    • getName

      public static String getName(Class<?> type)
      Gets the name of the given annotated class using the corresponding AnnotatedElementNameProvider strategy for the named annotation on the class. If no named annotations are present, then an empty string is returned. If no specified name is given by the name provider, then the simple name of the annotated class is returned.
      Parameters:
      type - annotated class to find name for
      Returns:
      annotated name of class
